<paragraph id="8BB6368C92457727FF43F814FBB8B46E" blockId="21.[136,1452,1144,2087]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FF43F814FE28BB95" bold="true" box="[189,441,1988,2014]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92457727FE47F815FD41BB95" box="[441,720,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92457727FE28F815FD41BB95" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[470,720,1989,2015]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">Bertolonia marmorata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B613CD192457727FD29F815FBB4B46E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798441301" location="Area de Protecao Ambiental Tinhare-Boipeba" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Bahia">
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992457727FC79F815FC6EBBAA" box="[903,1023,1989,2017]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8943" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" unit="km" value="78943.0">78,943 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992457727FB5FF814FA8DBBAA" box="[1185,1308,1988,2017]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" unit="km" value="25000.0">25,000 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Least Concern” (LC), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92457727FD4EF838FCD4B449" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[688,837,2024,2050]" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. In 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92457727FC17F838FBBCB449" box="[1001,1069,2024,2050]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="21" pageNumber="174">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, this species has been found in the “ 
<location id="8ED6605792457727FF6CF7DCFD0BB46E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A0879A92457725FF76FBE1FCBDBDB7:8ED6605792457727FF6CF7DCFD0BB46E" box="[146,666,2059,2087]" name="Area de Protecao Ambiental Tinhare-Boipeba" pageId="21" pageNumber="174" stateProvince="Bahia">Área de Proteção Ambiental Tinharé-Boipeba</location>
”, but also within private properties
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
