<subSubSection id="C313650792467725FF43F9AAFCBDBDB7" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92467725FF43F9AAFCBDBDB7" blockId="22.[136,1452,1658,2081]" lastBlockId="23.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF43F9AAFE98BADF" bold="true" box="[189,265,1658,1684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FED8F9AAFDB7BADF" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[294,550,1658,1684]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FED8F9AAFDB7BADF" box="[294,550,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92467724FCBEF9AAFC15BADF" box="[832,900,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92467724FC6FF9AAFC7CBADF" box="[913,1005,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92467724FBD2F9AAFB2DBADF" box="[1068,1212,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
. This species occurs in lowland rainforests, rarely in montane rainforests with some specimens distributed in transition areas between Atlantic Forest and Caatinga (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992467724FE23F912FDACBA97" box="[477,573,1730,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fig. 13c</figureCitation>
), usually on forested areas near water. Collected with flowers and fruits from October to February and July. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FE16F936FD76BB4B" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[488,743,1766,1792]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FE16F936FD76BB4B" box="[488,743,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the leaves with a rounded apex and flowers with small anthers (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992467724FE98F8DAFE4BBB6E" box="[358,474,1802,1829]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2 mm</quantity>
long) dehiscing through a triangular, introrse pore. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FBDFF8DAFA8FBB6F" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1057,1310,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FBDFF8DAFA8FBB6F" box="[1057,1310,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FF76F8FFFF66BB03" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[136,247,1839,1864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF76F8FFFF66BB03" box="[136,247,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. carmoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FECEF8FFFE2EBB03" box="[304,447,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FECEF8FFFE2ABB03" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[304,443,1838,1864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">B. maculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the limits between them is sometimes obscure (for more details, see the notes under both species). During this study we identified several specimens from different locations (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FB6EF882FA9CBB27" box="[1168,1293,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Aona 1841</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FAE3F882FA35BB27" box="[1309,1444,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bisewski 55</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF76F8A6FF35BBDB" box="[136,164,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">63</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF4DF8A7FEC3BBDB" box="[179,338,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Ferreira 1852</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FE9FF8A6FE65BBDB" box="[353,500,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fiaschi 2760</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FDFDF8A6FD57BBDB" box="[515,710,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">J.G. Jardim 4505</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FD2BF8A6FCFCBBDB" box="[725,877,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Thomas 3604</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FC85F8A6FC50BBDB" box="[891,961,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12500</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FC31F8A6FB84BBDB" box="[975,1045,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12505</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FBDDF8A6FBF8BBDB" box="[1059,1129,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12295</emphasis>
) that might belong to this 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FA6DF8A7FF61BBFF" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FA6DF8A7FF61BBFF" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FF06F84BFE07BBFF" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[248,406,1947,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF06F84BFE07BBFF" box="[248,406,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, They all share the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals covered with sessile or short-stalked glands (less than 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992467724FD73F86EFD75BB92" box="[653,740,1982,2009]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long) and long-stalked glands (
<quantity id="4CF19B6992467724FBB4F86EFB39BB92" box="[1098,1192,1982,2009]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
long), leaf blades with similar sizes (3–14.5 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992467724FE6BF832FDB5BBB6" box="[405,548,2018,2045]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="10.9" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="cm" value="6.65" valueMax="10.9" valueMin="2.4">2.4–10.9 cm</quantity>
) and anthers with an introrse pore (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992467724FC43F832FB8EBBB7" box="[957,1055,2018,2044]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[136,229,1198,1220]" captionTargetBox="[358,1229,190,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[358,1229,190,1173]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Specimens in vivo. A. Bertolonia igrapiuna. B. B. linearifolia. C. B. reginatoi. D. B. violacea. E. B. vitoriana. F. Bertolonia sp, belonging to the B. maculata/B. marmorata species complex. Photos:A, C and D by L. F. Bacci; B by F. Michelangeli; E and F by A. M. A. Amorim." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597710/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fig. 10e</figureCitation>
). Moreover, these specimens share with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92467724FF3CF7D7FEF1B46B" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[194,352,2055,2080]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92467724FF3CF7D7FEF1B46B" box="[194,352,2055,2080]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elliptic or widely ovate leaf blades with a rounded apex, similar anther size with an introrse, triangular pore. We are not sure about the inclusion of these specimens in the treatments for either 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FB1AFF4FFAFDBCF3" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1252,1388,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FB1AFF4FFAFDBCF3" box="[1252,1388,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FA6DFF4FFE97BC97" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FA6DFF4FFE97BC97" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly because these plants have a partially tuberous, thickened stem with plagiotropic growth, that stays hidden beneath the leaf litter; the plants are invisible during the dry season, when the deciduous leaves fall. The foliar portion of the stem seems to be thicker in periods with water availability, probably making it a water reserve structure. The development of this structure seems to be related to the habitat of the specimens; they usually occur in drier places, such as deciduous seasonal forest introgressions within the Caatinga. These observations were made in the field and still require further studies, including on the anatomy of these stems, in order to decide whether these specimens belong to either 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FEC0FE4BFE54BDFF" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[318,453,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FEC0FE4BFE54BDFF" box="[318,453,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FE15FE4BFD19BDFF" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[491,648,411,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FE15FE4BFD19BDFF" box="[491,648,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or even to one or more undescribed species. The whole 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FAFAFE4BFA1ABDFF" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1284,1419,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FAFAFE4BFA1ABDFF" box="[1284,1419,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92477725FA6DFE4BFE97BD93" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92477725FA6DFE4BFE97BD93" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex deserves a detailed, population-based study, in order to solve the problems on the limits of these species. For more details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92477725FE2EFE33FD0CBDB7" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[464,669,482,509]" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792477725FD2DFE32FCB7BDB7" box="[723,806,482,508]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
